Reference-contexts: To the best of our knowledge, the problem of classifying all such tuples for an arbitrary G is still open. (In a special case when k = 3, P 1 = B, and P 2 and P 3 are maximal parabolic subgroups, such a classification was given in <ref> [2] </ref>.) Here we present a complete solution of the classification problem for G = GL n . Let a = (a 0 ; : : : ; a p ) be a positive integer vector with the sum of components equal to n.
